values:
well.... It hasnt really been a month yet... guess Im trying to come back into gear!

Welp lets catch up...

*** W O R K ****
Interviewed for the tech position once again yesterday (3 in one), not sure about it. There's 4 positions open and 6 applied, from my understanding, I have the first dibs, since the "wanted" me last time, just didnt have enough positions... Wuteva. I really dont care if I get it or not.. Just started Floor Walking... meaning? It's a supervisoral position. I'm off the phones to assist others with questions and escalations (at which I tell the customer I AM the supervisor on the floor). So that's kewl! Just today was a killer... There's usually 2 floor walkers per team (approx 20-30 people per team) but today... one team was lacking... So myself and my fellow coworker/floor walker Bruselin had 60+ people to help. Very tiring! But I can take it.

**** K I D S ****
Phoebe and Charlie are doing great... Charlie (only several months old) is bigger than Phoebe! It's crazy, but I've worked more on the cages, (((stinkin ferrets are living better than i am))). They play all the time (and at times they're more entertaining than TV). You can see Phoebe is happy to have a play friend now... Still planning on "the Club".

**** L O V E *****
well....wouldnt go that far, but my significant other (Stephanie) and I are doing great. Am happy right now.. .still taking our time, just made the title - girlfriend.. here recently... made her day. She had to get her couch out of her house... her roommates (and their new dog) are ruining it... so I trashed mine and took her's in.. its an L shaped wrap around with recliner and hide away bed.. yeah, twist my arm... just spending time steam cleaning and shampooing it, but it looks nicer.

**** I3acI I3oy ****
doing good, had an infestation of ants... dont ask... dont know, but I think thats taken care of. still redoing it, makin her pretty (yes, her, with "boy" in the name, Get over it). Still planning on making a page to show my progress, when i get internet back at the house... which is coming soon... stayed tuned!

**** H O B B I E S ****
newbie.... One word.... Three Syllables..... AstroJax (www.astrojax.com). 
Having a blast with this space age "Yo Yo". It's been around for 10 years and is huge in the UK and Japan, just making way here in the states. Steph got me a set for a party I was throwing (a friend came into town and was going back home - party). played with them for a little while, then came to work and checked out the website and saw all the possibilities... been playing with it since!

***** C O N C L U S I O N *****

I think I'll wrap it up about here. Extremely tired and i need to go home! C U guys later!!!

PS. HAPPY BIRTHDAY MEG!!!! Im such a dork for forgetting!!! Specially after reminding me!

Yes Missy, but we can! Thank God we have gotten some rain, it was getting MAD hot! Now we have nice kewl nights..........

It's been a lil while, not too much has happened, not sure if thats a good thing or bad, but we'll go into that later tonight, but first, tonight's big story...

DID HE GET TECH??
and the answer.......no... but no biggie, not to sure if I would have liked the schedule anyways, and again, I like the team I'm on now. Good people, great Manager. So it's all good. Now here's Gawapo with the weather.... Gawapo...

CAR UPDATE...
operation CD Changer Relocation...complete, now I just need to smooth things out and paint it, I took a few pics, I'll work on getting up a lil web space to show the fun creativeness that took place on that lil project... now for those of you wondering about the Missing Link.....oh yeah.. the dash... Well its still in the living room, now I am able to work on it (being non-attached, and allowed to work on my own car now) BUT it still is taking some time, BUT check this! http://cgi.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?ViewItem&category=40017&item=2418908909 , thats right, I found a replacement for real cheap!! so it'll be that stock look again, but keeping it from being a "stripped" look. So one day at a time. 

Movie Note: 
Downloaded an excellent copy of the HULK screening, very nice, looks to be a good movie on the big screen. 2 Fast 2 Furious, dont know how many times I've seen it already, but it's great! Finding Nemo - awesome, has me in the market to get a salt water tank!

Well, gonna wrap this up here, I have a 2 hour training on new software we are upgrading to, and it's drawling near!

Oh on a side note....tomorrow, happy B day to me....anyways..

Confusious Says:
Baseball is wrong. Man with four balls cannot walk!

Ok, enough Whining...Vented, feel better, got these weird people on the internet talking to me and stuffin toy bears, then other people playin with my toys on my desk here. OFF MY ZIP ZAPS YO! Anyways, checking back. Man I can be a whiney brat. Glad that's out of my system!


now on with the Sour Apple Double Bubbles and Sweet tarts!

well I must say, 2 Fast 2 Furious was much better than I expected. Course I was purposely expecting it to not hold up to the first one....but, not having Vin Desil and adding Tyrese and Ludacris, was the best thing they could of done. If your not really into cars or didnt like the first one that much, I still recommend you see this movie. If you saw the first one and liked it......Then why haven't you seen the sequal??? Anyways.....

....it's raining, it's pouring, and I aint accomplishing squat! Just spending the day at the movies, catchin up on all the ones I missed so far.  Now that I'm takin a break, i just wanna chill and take a "Bob Ross" nap  (for those that know what that means). Guess its the constant rain....anyways here's a thought for ya 2 end it....


If your legs bent the other way......what would chairs look like? -CWH

In 1997, a crappy movie sequel came out that should have never made it to the big screen, but with that note, the soundtrack did not reflect on the stench for which the movie held. On the CD (or tape if you're still behind) contained a great collection for tranquil states to rage outbursts, all orchestrated in the closest form of perfection that could come about. But one song stands out the most, in this eclectic collection. It's called "Conga Fury" by a group named Juno Reactor. Now I do recommend you copy this song (illegally if you must) from the wonderful world of the web, and enjoy it. Or better yet......it was just recently mixed with some of my other loves: CGI and martial arts. Well if some of you haven't guessed where I'm getting with this right about now, I'm referring to "Final Flight of the Osiris", part of the Animatrix. Something I now watch as a routine in my day. I do recommend to at least seeing this short flick at least once!!!

Thought I would just share that.

well looks like i might have a good entry tonight
I've almost lost my mind!! Come into work, (as usual) take a few calls, everything is going kewl, then I get my one on one with my boss (it's a lil meeting held once a month with your boss to tell you what your doing right or wrong, and you go over a randomed picked call that was recorded, and are graded by that call), but everything went great there, no sweat. Get back on the phones, not even 2 mins in, I get a message to goto a certian room for my first interview for another position in the company (Tech). I take the interview during my normal lunch, so afterwards, I take a later than scheduled lunch, get back the phones, take one or two calls, and get an email to goto Quality (another "One on One" just with another person. ) Now we're suppose to get two or three of these per month, its now June 4th, and I'm slammed with two in a row (very rare), Did great there too, got a new QA (Quality Associate) I hated my last one. Its like school here, with teachers you dont like, grading you on your progress. Anyways, as I'm on my way back to my desk, I hear my name hollered out loud, and told to get in a close by room for my Second interview for the Tech postion....which I did well til the very end where they slam this question on you and you BOMB!! I found out, everyone studdered and messed up on that point. So it's like a trick to mess with your head. Thanx guys. Anyways, I'm drained and don't know to wind my butt or scratch my watch! Now it's time to go home!! 
Hopefully these things wont be this long, but who knows....the way I ramble!!

Welp, lets give this a lil whirl.
I've been told that I keep to myself too much, but I thought I talk about myself WAAAAYY too much!
So a good friend turned me on to this lil journal deal, that I could "blah blah blah" in, and my friends could check out whats going on in my life. 
Sounds boring to me, but I'll give it a lil whirl.
